FBIS4-25858 "drchi115_j_94001" FBIS-CHI-94-115 Daily Report 13 Jun 1994 Latin America & Caribbean Wu Bangguo-Led CPC Delegation Leaves Cuba for Home Wu Bangguo-Led CPC Delegation Leaves Cuba for Home OW1406132794 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0241 GMT 13 Jun 94 OW1406132794 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service Chinese BFN [By reporter Hou Yaoqi (0186 5069 0366)] [Text] Havana, 12 Jun (XINHUA) -- After concluding a week-long visit to Cuba, a CPC delegation led by Wu Bangguo, member of the CPC Central Committee Political Bureau and secretary of the Shanghai Municipal CPC Committee, left Havana for home on 12 June. Ross Leal, politburo member of the Communist Party of Cuba [PCC] Central Committee, vice president of the Council of State, and executive secretary general of the Council of Ministers; Jose Balaguer, politburo member of the PCC Central Committee and director of the PCC Central Committee's International Relations Department; and Chinese Ambassador to Cuba Xu Yicong saw off the delegation at the airport. The CPC delegation arrived in Cuba on 6 June for a visit at the invitation of the PCC. During its visit, Fidel Castro, first secretary of the PCC Central Committee, president of the Council of State, and president of the Council of Ministers met with all members of the delegation, attended a reception hosted by Ambassador Xu Yicong for the delegation, and held a long, cordial conversation with Wu Bangguo. Wu Bangguo and his party separately held talks and had contacts with Leal, Balaguer, and other party and government leaders to exchange views on wide-ranging issues of common concern. Meanwhile, they visited some factories, scientific research and medical care units, and municipal administration and tourism facilities.
